<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Humbleness" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Humbleness,</orth> 1) absence of pride, submissiveness: <bibl n="shak. mv 1.3.125" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 3, 125</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 5.2.103" default="NO" valid="yes">As V, 2, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.117" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 V, 1, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 4.2.4" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 4</bibl>.<lb />2) benevolence, kindness; <cit><quote>which h. may drive unto a fine,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mv 4.1.372" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. IV, 1, 372</bibl></cit> (i. e. kindness on the part of the signiory).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>